description: Avoid reading secret-bearing env files
alwaysApply: true
---

# Secret File Guardrail

- Do not read `.env`, `.env.*`, or other secret-bearing local config files unless the user explicitly asks, or there is no safer way to complete the task.
- Prefer `src/config.ts`, `.env.example`, docs, or direct user confirmation when checking runtime configuration.
- If a secret-bearing file must be inspected, keep access minimal and never persist secret values into memory, docs, commits, or summaries.
